ğŸ—’ï¸ Notes (Principles â€¢ Compatibility â€¢ Privacy)

Principles
	â€¢	ATS-first, human-friendly: single column, clean spacing, consistent bullets, clear page breaks.
	â€¢	Evidence-only: never fabricate achievements; if metrics are missing, we ask for them (Accomplishment Nudge).
	â€¢	Clarity: expand acronyms on first mention (e.g., Applicant Tracking System (ATS)), then keep them short.

Compatibility
	â€¢	Best with DOCX and PDF; RTF fallback ensures universal openability without losing structure.
	â€¢	OCR improves screenshot parsing when available; otherwise users get a polite nudge to upload a text-based file.

Privacy
	â€¢	ATS copy hides phone number and street address by default (you can switch this off).
	â€¢	No analytics required to generate documents.

Accessibility
	â€¢	Clean, single-column structure improves screen-reader parsing; body text in readable sizes by default.

